[MESSAGE]Excellent! Now let's talk about how you're going to set up a live performance for your restaurant. Live performances help improve your restaurant rating which, in turn, helps attract more customers. To start, let's find out what performances are available to you.

Open the _Report List_ under the _Information Center_ to proceed.
[POSITION]475,32
[DIMENSION]310,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]Under the _Report List_, you will find the _Performance List_ displaying all the live performances currently available. As you can see, you can only hire "%s" to perform in your restaurant for now. As you meet and talk with different people, your selection of available performers for hire will expand as a result.

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]475,32
[DIMENSION]310,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]The _Performance List_ gives you a view of each live performer's stats and requirements.

Different performers require different stages to put on their show. By clicking on the performer "%s", you can see which performance stages are suitable for his performance.

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]475,32
[DIMENSION]310,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]As mentioned, performers will only be able to perform their acts when you have provided them with their proper performance stage. Let's give this a try then.

You can find the royalty performance stage under the _Accessory_ category of the _Interior Panel_. Now clear up some space and add the performance stage to your dining hall.

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]475,32
[DIMENSION]310,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]Good job! Let's now assign the performer to this stage.

_Double Left-lick_ on the performance stage to view the item's properties.
[POSITION]475,32
[DIMENSION]310,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]This is the _Performance Detail_ interface. You'll notice there is currently no live performance linked to this stage. We'll need to add one then.

_Left-click_ on the _Add Performance_ button to proceed.
[POSITION]475,32
[DIMENSION]310,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]The _Performance List_ interface shows all the performances available to this particular stage.  To assign an act to your stage, highlight the performer and left click OK to assign him to it. When you already have a performer assigned but no longer wish to avail of his services, you can select "No Performance" to remove him.

Highlight the performer "%s" and _Left-click_ on the _OK_ button to continue.
[POSITION]475,32
[DIMENSION]310,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]Well Done! You have just assigned "%s" to the performance stage.

_Double Left-lick_ on the performance stage to review the details of this performance.
[POSITION]475,32
[DIMENSION]310,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]The performance will be paid according to the hourly rate and the act's duration. A longer duration will better improve your restaurant rating but will naturally be more expensive.

Let's change the performance start time to %02d:%02d and the duration to %d hour(s).

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]475,32
[DIMENSION]310,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]Great! You have now finished setting up the live performance. But before we wrap, there is one final thing to see.

Open the _Reports_ under the _Information Center_ interface to proceed.
[POSITION]475,32
[DIMENSION]310,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]Under the _Reports_, find the Restaurant Rating category. The live performance's effect on your restaurant is shown under the _Environment Rating_. Your restaurant's rating is improved according to the performance's rating and duration. Always keep in mind that removing a performance will reset the accumulated Live Performance rating of the restaurant. Also note that adjusting a stage's position will not have an effect on the performance rating. And that's it for live performances. By following these simple steps and fiddling around it some more and your restaurant will be buzzing with entertainment in no time.
